>
>> Does anyone have any good ideas about what the best way to 
>>utilize the luggage rack on top of my 74 westy??? 
>
>Put anything up there that 1.) you don't mind getting wet or 
wind-blown, 2.) 
>isn't overly-inviting to theft, and 3.) you don't have to 
access very often.  
>It's a pain putting multiple things up there.  I once loaded 
mine up with 
>firewood for a campout.  Took forever to load it and way to 
long to unload it 
>and I was afraid the whole drive up that the logs would come 
loose and go 
>bouncing along the highway.
>
>Just remember, whatever you put up there makes your bus 
taller.  A Westy with 
>nothing on top will pass through most parking garages and 
drive-throughs.  Add  
>more than a few inches and you may not fit anymore!
>
>Mike g.
>73 Westy
